-- Saudi Ministry Appoints Woman to Senior Post, Arab News Reports
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-03T05:45:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/saudi-ministry-appoints-woman-to-senior-post-arab-news-reports.html
Saudi Arabia  appointed a woman as an
assistant undersecretary at the Ministry of Health as part of
government restructuring to improve public services,  Arab News 
reported, citing Health Ministry spokesman Khalid al-Mirghalani  Muneera bint Hamdan al-Osaimi was the first woman to be
appointed to this position at the ministry, the Jeddah-based
newspaper reported. Her title is assistant undersecretary for
medical services affairs, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  